{"title":"The Ritchey P-29er is Back & Updated Making it the Ultimate Cross-Country Mountain Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/the-ritchey-p-29er-is-back-updated-making-it-the-ultimate-cross-country-mountain-bike/","date":1718390702000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" alt=\"(Photos/Ritchey Bikes)\" /></p>\n<p>Cross Country riders rejoice! The Ritchey <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/product/p-29er-frame?goal=0_a8437982ed-46018b0ba4-227528490&amp;mc_cid=46018b0ba4&amp;mc_eid=f0975ec951\" target=\"_blank\">P-29er </a>is back and better than ever. The latest manifestation of the P-29er reflects Tom Ritchey’s decades-long history/knowledge of the mountain bike. The frameset is designed for “ripping tight, twisty, and technical cross-country singletrack.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset hero 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-hero-2-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Ritchey Bikes)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey</a> uses their iconic, proprietary triple-butted Logic steel tubing for the frameset. Thus, combining modern progressive, XC geometry which provides a “balanced” ride that mixes “a snappy, responsive soul with a comfortable and predictable personality”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset p-29er logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-p-29er-logo-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The P-29er carries with it a pedigree that is firmly rooted in the decades-deep lineage of its P-Series predecessors, helping define the sport of mountain biking. This version of the modern P-29er is loaded with features demanded by today’s XC riders. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-bottom-bracket-cluster.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"886\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-bottom-bracket-cluster.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset bottom bracket cluster\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-bottom-bracket-cluster.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-bottom-bracket-cluster-297x206.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-bottom-bracket-cluster-120x83.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-bottom-bracket-cluster-768x532.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset Machined and forged headtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Machined-and-forged-headtube-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It has BOOST spacing along with stealthy dropper post routing. Plus, it carries an ultralight, forged, and machined tapered headtube. The frame has tire spacing for tires up to 2.3 and is designed to run a 100mm travel fork. This frame is ready for endless singletrack adventures.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset unique brake brace\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-unique-brake-brace-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ritchey P-29er Geo</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Geo.jpg\"><img width=\"410\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Geo.jpg\" alt=\"Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Geo.jpg\n\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Geo.jpg 410w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Geo-297x249.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Geo-120x101.jpg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset jumpin' roots\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-jumpin-roots-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset riding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-riding-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ritchey P-29er Retail &amp; Specs </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $999</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes: S (15”), M (17”), L (19”), XL (21”)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame material: heat-treated, triple-butted Ritchey Logic steel tubing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ultra-light Forged and machined tapered headtube</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Optimized for 100mm (BOOST) suspension travel fork or 500mm axle-crown rigid fork</li>\n\n\n\n<li>BOOST 148 x 12mm rear end with replaceable stainless steel derailleur hanger</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Post-mount rear brake: 160mm (180mm max – adaptors available separately)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Headset: WCS headset included (upper IS42/28.6 | lower IS52/40)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Recommended tire size: 29×2.25 (2.3 max) (depending on tire/rim manufacturer)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bottle cage mounts: Two (one on downtube and one on seat tube) *Note: one on size S</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Designed for 1X chainrings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>27.2mm seat tube with stealth dropper routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bottom Bracket: 73mm English</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: 2,380 g/5.25 lbs (M/17”)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Color: Dirt in Blood</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom.jpeg\" alt=\"Ritchey P-29er Frameset Designed by tom\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ritchey-P-29er-Frameset-Designed-by-tom-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>Tom Ritchey is known for taking whatever bike project he’s working on to the limit and then pushing beyond that in the redesign phase. This latest P-29er perfectly demonstrates his indisputable design style and his tendency toward new thinking to make something great even better</em>“</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The P-29er is available globally at the link below, <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=93d6318dfc980cc0e664e8c59&amp;id=754fd7f564&amp;e=f0975ec951\" target=\"_blank\">Certified Ritchey Assemblers</a>, <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=93d6318dfc980cc0e664e8c59&amp;id=14e72c1667&amp;e=f0975ec951\" target=\"_blank\">local bike shops</a>, and <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.us13.list-manage.com/track/click?u=93d6318dfc980cc0e664e8c59&amp;id=3349e0832f&amp;e=f0975ec951\" target=\"_blank\">online retailers</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">RitcheyLogic.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-ritchey-p-29er-is-back-updated-making-it-the-ultimate-cross-country-mountain-bike/\">The Ritchey P-29er is Back &amp; Updated Making it the Ultimate Cross-Country Mountain Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7b19d815efd8aed039aee8369df0ea90a99988ce8841cb0f87740285eb66c7bc","category":"Cycling"}